<subsection xml:id="subsec-table-of-values-for-linear-equations">
    <title>Table of Values for Linear Equations</title>
    <activity>
        <p>
            <m>{\color{black} \textbf{Work in groups}}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Consider the linear equation <m>\textbf{y = 2x + 1}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            Create a table of values by choosing different <m>\textbf{x-values}</m> and calculating <m>y</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
            Discuss and share the results with other groups
        </p>
    </activity>
    <p>
        <m>{\color{black} \textbf{Key Takeaway}}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        A linear equation is usually in the form <m>\textbf{y = mx + b}</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        where <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <m>m</m> is the slope (rate of change).
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <m>b</m> is the y-intercept (where the line crosses the y-axis).
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <p>
        A table of values helps us organize points that satisfy a linear equation. 
    </p>
    <p>
        By substituting different values of x, we calculate corresponding y-values to create a set of ordered pairs <m>(x,y)</m>
    </p>
    <p>
        These points can then be plotted on a Cartesian plane to form a straight line.
    </p>
    <example>
        <statement>
            <p>
                Complete the table of values for the linear equation:
            </p>
            <p>
                <m>\textbf{y = -x + 4}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                for example,<m>x</m> = <m>2</m> then
            </p>
            <p>
                 <m>\textbf{y = -2 + 4}</m> 
            </p>
            <p>
                = <m>2</m>
            </p>
            
            <tabular halign="left" top="medium" left="medium" right="medium" bottom="medium" width="auto" >
                <row>
                    <cell>x</cell>                    
                    <cell>-2</cell>                
                    <cell>-1</cell>
                    <cell>0</cell>
                    <cell>1</cell>
                    <cell>2</cell>
                    
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>y</cell>
                    <cell>?</cell>
                    <cell>?</cell>
                    <cell>?</cell>
                    <cell>?</cell>
                    <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p>
                
            </p>
                
            <tabular halign="left" top="medium" left="medium" right="medium" bottom="medium">
                <row>
                    <cell>x</cell>
                    <cell>Calculation</cell>
                    <cell>y Value</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>-2</cell>
                    <cell><m>\textbf{y = −(−2) + 4 = 2 + 4}</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>6</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>-1</cell>
                    <cell><m>\textbf{y = −(−1) + 4 = 1 + 4}</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>5</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>0</cell>
                    <cell><m>\textbf{y = −(0) + 4 = 0 + 4}</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>4</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>1</cell>
                    <cell><m>\textbf{y = −(1) + 4 = −1 + 4}</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>3</m></cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>2</cell>
                    <cell><m>\textbf{y = −(2) + 4 = −2 + 4}</m></cell>
                    <cell><m>2</m></cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
        </solution>
    </example>
    
</subsection>